    "description": "A Metagenomics Analytical Framework for Routine Biosurveillance and Clinical Pathogen Detection.\n\nThe bioinformatics pipeline leverages BWA/Minimap2 to identify \u2018where\u2019 reads belong to provides taxonomy identification specific to strain-level. Other than community profiling, PanGIA uses two approaches to obtain a metric of confidence, one that relies on uniqueness of sequences and the other one that relies on comparing test samples with control samples (organism-basis).",
